"{\"uid\": \"independent.co.uk-sport-olympics-paris-2024-olympics-seine-dirty-coke-b2593723.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Notifications can be managed in browser preferences.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in  Swipe for next article  Water quality concerns have prompted teams to drop out and swim trials to be postponed  Removed from bookmarks  I would like to be emailed about offers, events and updates from The Independent.\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 409, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy notice  Olympic swimmers, some of the healthiest people on the planet, are turning to an unlikely, unscientific solution to ward off getting sick from competing in the polluted waters of the Seine in Paris: drinking cans of Coke.\", \"from\": 410, \"to\": 655, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 617, \"end\": 622, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9942166514651409, \"rank\": 0.005816960362997569, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 626, \"end\": 631, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999938686388917, \"rank\": 6.131398589228751e-06, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Top swimmers swear by the stuff to prevent infection, according to athletes of three teams whospoke withThe Wall Street Journal.\", \"from\": 657, \"to\": 785, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 765, \"end\": 784, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Wall_Street_Journal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.906139864445992e-28, \"text\": \"Wall Street Journal\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Wall_Street_Journal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Wall_Street_Journal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The myth of Coca-Cola is true,\\\" Moesha Johnson of Team Australia, said.\", \"from\": 787, \"to\": 859, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 800, \"end\": 809, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coca-Cola\", \"score\": 0.9999228558552982, \"rank\": 7.715009626345241e-05, \"text\": \"Coca-Cola\", \"types\": [\"Q2095\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coca-Cola\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coca-Cola\"}, {\"begin\": 838, \"end\": 852, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_Australia\", \"score\": 0.9998832357117852, \"rank\": 0.00011677792362996913, \"text\": \"Team Australia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We will often have a Coca-Cola afterward just to try to flush out anything inside of us.\\\"\", \"from\": 860, \"to\": 950, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 882, \"end\": 891, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coca-Cola\", \"score\": 0.9999228558552982, \"rank\": 7.715009626345241e-05, \"text\": \"Coca-Cola\", \"types\": [\"Q2095\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coca-Cola\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coca-Cola\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That strategy, which swimmers from the US, New Zealand, and Italy all discussed with the paper, may not be scientifically sound, even if it's popular.\", \"from\": 952, \"to\": 1102, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 991, \"end\": 993, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9997519602971829, \"rank\": 0.00013814220998215163, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 995, \"end\": 1006, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.611982066751581, \"rank\": 0.4010697544212899, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dr Maria Abreu, president of the American Gastroenterological Association, told theJournalthat Coke is less acidic than a healthy stomach, meaning it likely would not add any infection-fighting power.\", \"from\": 1104, \"to\": 1304, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1107, \"end\": 1112, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hurricane_Maria\", \"score\": 0.9994019470853829, \"rank\": 0.0005922385130936587, \"text\": \"Maria\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hurricane_Maria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hurricane_Maria\"}, {\"begin\": 1113, \"end\": 1118, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bobby_Abreu\", \"score\": 0.897106574309386, \"rank\": 0.11469475905557043, \"text\": \"Abreu\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bobby_Abreu\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bobby_Abreu\"}, {\"begin\": 1137, \"end\": 1177, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Gastroenterological_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"American Gastroenterological Association\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Gastroenterological_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Gastroenterological_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"These are young, athletic people, right?\", \"from\": 1306, \"to\": 1347, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They are going to be healthy people whose stomach acid is going to be nice and robust,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 1348, \"to\": 1445, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Water quality in the Seine has been a persistent concern in Paris so far.\", \"from\": 1447, \"to\": 1520, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1468, \"end\": 1473, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9942166514651409, \"rank\": 0.005816960362997569, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 1507, \"end\": 1512, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999938686388917, \"rank\": 6.131398589228751e-06, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Swimming in the river haslargely been prohibited for the last centurybecause it's been too toxic.\", \"from\": 1521, \"to\": 1618, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite French officials spending $1.5bn on infrastructure improvements ahead of the games, including to make the Seine cleaner, issues have persisted.\", \"from\": 1620, \"to\": 1771, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1628, \"end\": 1634, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9924686439152257, \"rank\": 0.007057639440282834, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1734, \"end\": 1739, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9942166514651409, \"rank\": 0.005816960362997569, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A test run of the marathon swim course in the Seine waspostponeduntil today over concerns about water quality, though the triathlon mixed relay went ahead as planned the day before.\", \"from\": 1773, \"to\": 1954, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1819, \"end\": 1824, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9942166514651409, \"rank\": 0.005816960362997569, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Last week, Belgiumpulled its team from the mixed relay eventafter an athlete who previously swam in the river got sick, and a swimmer for Switzerland alsomissed the competitiondue to illness.\", \"from\": 1956, \"to\": 2147, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2094, \"end\": 2105, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"score\": 0.9999943711672298, \"rank\": 5.2901715522254055e-06, \"text\": \"Switzerland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Last month, Paris mayor Anne Hidalgo swam in the Seine to assure athletes about the river's safety.\", \"from\": 2149, \"to\": 2248, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2161, \"end\": 2166, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999938686388917, \"rank\": 6.131398589228751e-06, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2173, \"end\": 2185, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anne Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\"}, {\"begin\": 2198, \"end\": 2203, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9942166514651409, \"rank\": 0.005816960362997569, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"So I am really proud and happy and to all those who want to continue saying it's impossible to depollute a river, I tell them, 'Yes it's possible, we did it,'\\\" shesaidrecently.\", \"from\": 2250, \"to\": 2427, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite these reassurances, some argue swimming the Seine was never a good idea.\", \"from\": 2429, \"to\": 2509, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2481, \"end\": 2486, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9942166514651409, \"rank\": 0.005816960362997569, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I would never have selected the Seine,\\\" Davey Jones, professor of Environmental science and public health at Bangor University,told BBC Science Focus.\", \"from\": 2511, \"to\": 2662, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2544, \"end\": 2549, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9942166514651409, \"rank\": 0.005816960362997569, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 2621, \"end\": 2638, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bangor_University\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bangor University\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bangor_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bangor_University\"}, {\"begin\": 2644, \"end\": 2661, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_Science_Focus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"BBC Science Focus\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_Science_Focus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_Science_Focus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I know it's iconic, but it also runs through a hugely urbanised area which is always a recipe